lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO, Sept. 18 — Intel gave the first public demonstration on Tuesday of a new generation of computer processors that significantly increase performance without consuming more power.

abstract: Intel announced that it is acquiring Havok, the Irish developer of the widely used physics engine of the same name.
